                        <div class='side-b-body' id='kayak-body'>
                            <div class='rental-catagory-main'>
                                <div class='rentals-body-top'>
                                    <h1 class='rentals-title'>
                                        Kayak Rentals
                                    </h1>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class='rentals-body-middle'>
                                <p>
                                    Kayaking is a watersport that allows you to enjoy nature from a different perspective. It can be a calm and relaxing experience set on a mellow lake or a fun and exciting adventure on the rapids of your local river. You decide. The possibilities for kayaking are endless. If you’re thinking about kayaking, Hillcrest Sports offers daily and seasonal kayak rentals. We carry a full range of kayaks including single kayaks and tandem kayaks-- so you can explore alone or with a friend! Our kayak rentals start at the low price of $ 49 and come with everything you need to have a safe kayaking experience including your paddles and your personal flotation device (PFD). We also offer recreational passes in-store.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class='rentals-prices'>
                                <div class='rentals-price-catagory'>
                                    <h2>Kayak Prices</h2>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li class='white'>1 Day</li>
                                        <li>3 Day</li>
                                        <li class='white'>1 Week</li>
                                    </ul>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li class='white'>$49</li>
                                        <li>$90</li>
                                        <li class='white'>$149</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class='rentals-body-bottom'>
                                <h2>
                                    Where to Kayak
                                </h2>
                                <p>
                                    There are several popular kayaking spots in the Portland OR and Vancouver WA area. Whether you want to stay close to home and kayak on Sauvie Island or Vancouver Lake or venture out toward the mountains and try Trillium Lake and Frog Lake, we will help you find an ideal kayaking spot catered to your skill level. Remember recreation passes can be purchased at our store as well, so pick up your pass and head to one of the many popular kayaking destinations our beautiful area has to offer.
                                </p>
                                <h2>
                                    Transport Kayaks
                                </h2>
                                <p>
                                    If you’re thinking about renting a kayak, you’ll want to consider how you’re going to transport it. There are a variety of ways to safely transport a kayak. Kayaks can be tied down to your vehicle with cam straps and water-resistant rope. You can also invest in a roof rack or smaller trailer to making transporting your kayak effortless.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class='side-b-body' id='paddleboard-body'>
                            <div class='rental-catagory-main'>
                                <div class='rentals-body-top'>
                                    <h1 class='rentals-title'>
                                        Paddleboard Rentals
                                    </h1>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class='rentals-body-middle'>
                                <p>
                                    Stand up paddle boarding has become quite popular recently in the world of watersports. Stand up paddle boarding (SUP) allows you explore the water without having to swim in it. It’s quite like surfing only you stand still and move yourself around using a paddle.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class='rentals-prices'>
                                <div class='rentals-price-catagory'>
                                    <h2>Paddleboard</br>Prices</h2>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li class='white'>1 Day</li>
                                        <li>3 Day</li>
                                        <li class='white'>1 Week</li>
                                    </ul>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li class='white'>$49</li>
                                        <li>$90</li>
                                        <li class='white'>$149</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class='rentals-body-bottom'>
                                <h2>
                                    Paddle Board Rental
                                </h2>
                                <p>
                                    If you’re interested in paddle boarding at one of our local waterways, Hillcrest Sports provides stand up paddle board rentals. Our rentals are only $40 for the day. You’ll receive the paddle board (either inflatable or hardboard) a paddle, and your personal floatation device (FPD) all for 24 hours. If you need the equipment for more than 24 hours, we also provide longer rentals.
                                </p>
                                <h2>
                                    Where to Paddle Board
                                </h2>
                                <p>
                                    Here in the Portland OR and Vancouver WA area, there are several popular places to go paddle boarding. Take in the breathtaking views of Mt. Hood at Trillium Lake located in the Mt. Hood National Forest or stay closer to home and head out to Vancouver Lake -- which is a great spot for beginners. Most places require a day use fee, but to make it convenient, we sell recreational passes in-store. So when you stop by to pick up your rental, you can pick up your pass at the same time!
                                </p>
                                <h2>
                                    Transporting Your Paddle Board
                                </h2>
                                <p>
                                    One thing to keep in mind with your paddle board rental is how you’ll be transporting it. You can invest in a rack to fit in the back of your truck or car or invest in a small trailer that’s capable of transporting several paddle boards at one time. You can also tie it down by using straps and the crossbars installed on the roof of your vehicle.
                                </p>
                                <h2>
                                    Reserve Your Paddle Board
                                </h2>
                                <p>
                                    Once you’re ready to give stand up paddle boarding a try, contact Hillcrest Sports for your paddle board rental. We’ll teach you the basics and then have you on your way.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class='side-b-body' id='wake-sports-body'>
                            <div class='rental-catagory-main'>
                                <div class='rentals-body-top'>
                                    <h1 class='rentals-title'>
                                        Wake Sports Rentals
                                    </h1>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class='rentals-body-middle'>
                                <p>
                                    Wakeboards and Wakesurf Boards, while previously belived to be one singular type of object. It had been revieled by Ryan that they are in fact two seperate things. One is a different shape than the other. Wakeboarding is a water sport in which the rider, standing on a wakeboard (a short board with foot bindings), is towed behind a motorboat across its wake and especially up off the crest in order to perform aerial maneuvers. Wakesurfing is a water sport in which a rider trails behind a boat, riding the boat's wake without being directly pulled by the boat. 
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class='rentals-prices'>
                                <div class='rentals-price-catagory'>
                                    <h2>Wake Sport</br>Prices</h2>
